Package: MiningCostBench
Type: Package
Title: Benchmark Production Costs and Cost Drivers for Mining Commodities
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Manoj", "Kumar", email = "you@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")))
Description: A curated, citable data package of indicative cash/production cost
    ranges and structured cost-driver breakdowns for mining and mineral
    commodities, organised by category: coal and lignite by rank, base metals,
    precious metals, fuel and atomic minerals, India's 30 critical minerals,
    and bulk/industrial minerals. Each commodity carries a six-stage cost-driver
    decomposition (extraction, processing, energy/reagents, logistics,
    fiscal/ESG and structural), a by-product flag, and a separate table of
    cross-cutting cost drivers. Notes and indicative sources are bundled so the
    figures remain traceable. Intended as an orientation and teaching dataset,
    not a substitute for a commercial cost-curve service.
